\[a_k = b_{k-1} + k\]

Since \(k = n - 1\), we have:

\[a_k = (b_{k-1} + k) = b_{k-1} + k = b_{k-1} + (n - 1)\]

Thus, \(k = n - 1\) ensures that \(a_k\) matches the given condition. Therefore, the solution is \(k = n - 1\).
